Job Title: Senior AI/ML Architect, Applied Field Engineering
Ad Text:
Snowflake is about empowering enterprises to achieve their full potential — and people too. With a culture that’s all in on impact, innovation, and collaboration, Snowflake is the sweet spot for building big, moving fast, and taking technology — and careers — to the next level.

Our Solution Engineering organization is seeking an AI Specialist who can provide hands-on expertise and support while working with technical decision makers and data scientists to design and architect AI solutions built on the Snowflake AI Data Cloud.

This is a strategic role that works closely with cross-functional teams, including product, engineering, and the broader field organization to ensure successful execution and customer adoption of Snowflake’s AI & ML solutions.


IN THIS ROLE YOU WILL GET TO:


Be the technical expert in the room that positions Snowflake’s AI and ML features and value to technical stakeholders at Snowflake’s customers across the APJ region.

Partner with Snowflake account team teams and customer champions to scope and drive POCs to success and technical wins that prove the value of Snowflake’s capabilities, including executive readouts and business value cases.

Collaborate with Snowflake’s product and engineering teams to influence Snowflake’s AI and ML roadmaps based on customer feedback.

Publish content that helps the team and company scale beyond your individual efforts, like blog posts, presentations at conferences, or technical collateral like notebooks and demos.

Influence, tailor and maintain Solution Engineering AI and ML selling assets, including customer presentations, demonstrations, and customer stories.

Work with account teams across APJ region to help customers adopt AI/ML use cases on Snowflake

ON DAY ONE, WE WILL EXPECT YOU TO HAVE:


5+ years of experience building and deploying machine learning and generative AI solutions in the cloud.

Familiarity and associated knowledge of generative AI techniques like RAG, few shot learning, prompt engineering, or fine-tuning that are used to operationalize enterprise AI use cases like interactive chat applications or text processing.

Deep knowledge of Python and common ML packages (such as LangChain, pandas, sklearn, and PyTorch) as well as data engineering tools and technologies like dbt, Airflow, and Spark.

Strong presentation skills to both technical and executive audiences, whether whiteboarding sessions or formal readouts and demos.

Bachelor’s Degree required, Masters Degree in computer science, engineering, mathematics or related fields, or equivalent experience preferred.

BONUS POINTS FOR EXPERIENCE WITH THE FOLLOWING:


Working knowledge of tools in the LLM ecosystem such as LangChain, LlamaIndex, or other OSS packages.

Experience and understanding of large-scale infrastructure-as-a-service platforms (e.g. AWS, Microsoft Azure, GCP, etc.)

1+ years of practical Snowflake experience.

Knowledge of and experience with large-scale database technology (e.g. Snowflake, Netezza, Exadata, Teradata, Greenplum, etc.)

Working experience with quota carrying roles in the past.

Snowflake is growing fast, and we’re scaling our team to help enable and accelerate our growth. We are looking for people who share our values, challenge ordinary thinking, and push the pace of innovation while building a future for themselves and Snowflake.

How do you want to make your impact?

The ideal candidate will be responsible for:

Provide subject matter expertise on technical solutions and serve as the primary technical contact for the design and implementation of Unified Communications (UC) capabilities, ensuring scalability, security, and efficiency.

Develop UC roadmaps in collaboration with internal stakeholders, including architecture, design, and cybersecurity teams.

Support solution design and implementation for communication, collaboration, and networking systems.

Maintain UC systems and services, including telephony, collaboration platforms, messaging, desktop and softphones, mobile devices, PBX systems, and voice/video conferencing environments.

Create and maintain policies, procedures, and training plans for system administration and appropriate use.

Research emerging technologies—products, services, protocols, and standards—to inform procurement and development efforts.

Collaborate with cross-functional teams to ensure architectural alignment and consistency across projects.

Engage stakeholders to address design and security challenges, provide solutions to complex infrastructure and software issues, and deliver technical support for UC system upgrades.

Mandatory Skills & Experience:

10+ years of experience in designing, deploying and managing UC systems and solutions.

Strong stakeholder management and client services skills.

Ability to articulate technical detail through detailed design and implementation plans.

Highly developed diagnostic and problem-solving skills.

Ability to work effectively as a team member.

Excellent communication skills, both written and oral.

A broad understanding of industry, whole of government direction, emerging technologies and how they can be applied to solve business problems.

Experience in the day-to-day operations of Unified Communications systems and solutions, including the management of voice and data transmissions through the deployment, monitoring, troubleshooting and optimising of the workflow of UC systems (voice, video and VoIP).

A strong understanding of ASD Essential 8 and experience with contributing to security accreditation of ICT systems.

Progressive experience and familiarity with current and emerging networking and collaboration technologies.

Candidates must hold NV1 security clearance or higher.

The candidate must have exceptional communication skills who can lean into complex conversations and offer technical solutions that creates buy-in from stakeholders with varying technical and non-technical backgrounds.

If you are looking for a change and might be interested in applying, please get in touch with Manni at enquiries@vlinked.com.au for more details.

About the team

The Sensing Engineering team at Q-CTRL transforms quantum research into deployable technologies that address real-world problems. We design, build, and field-validate an array of quantum sensors that support our key products, including Ironestone Opal - our solution for GPS-denied navigation.   

You don’t need a background in quantum to make an impact here. We value strong engineering fundamentals, a product mindset, and a drive to solve the hardest engineering problems in quantum sensing today.

About the role

We are seeking an Embedded Software Engineer to develop firmware for our control, sensing, and actuation systems that automate the operation of our quantum sensors. You’ll primarily be developing new applications on our Xilinx Zynq + Embedded Linux platform based on requirements developed in collaboration with our research scientists to assist scientific advancement and to demonstrate our technology in the field. Our firmware is characterised by real-time constraints, data acquisition, signal processing, sequence execution, network communication, and hardware/FPGA interfacing. You will join a growing team focused on quantum sensing for defence and aerospace, and work with experts in fields such as cold-atom interferometry, magnetometry, and inertial navigation to develop state-of-the-art technology.

What you’ll be doing:

Own the design, development, integration, and support of embedded systems employed in Q-CTRL’s quantum sensing and navigation systems targeting Xilinx SoC and STM32 platforms.
Responsible for the design, implementation, and testing of control, sensing, and actuation firmware needed to autonomously operate next generation quantum sensors.
Work as a technical lead and architect in cross-functional teams of scientists and engineers to solve novel issues in research & development and product-focused environments.
Contribute to the success of field trials with industry partners
Create test and simulation setups including hardware-in-the-loop test fixtures.
Other duties within the Employee’s skills and experience, or with reasonable training.
Ideally you’ll have:

Experience working in a research environment whilst collaborating with established engineering teams and research scientists.
Experience in algorithm development for control systems and autonomous sensor operation.
Experience as a technical lead or domain expert working as a subject matter expert in a cross functional team
Proficiency with a systems programming language such as C, C++, or Rust.
Experience with a hardware description language (Verilog/VHDL)
Experience creating embedded linux distributions using tools such as Buildroot, Yocto, or Petalinux.
Experience using an RTOS to develop microcontroller firmware.
Desirable to have worked on embedded systems involving interfacing with FPGAs such as JESD204 and AXI interfaces.
Preference will be given to candidates with experience qualifying or deploying systems for use in aircraft.

About Q-CTRL

Q-CTRL is the global leader in AI-powered quantum control infrastructure software. We build the tools that make quantum technology useful, solving the hardest challenges in quantum computing and quantum sensing to deliver real-world impact.

Founded in 2017, we operate globally with offices in Sydney, Los Angeles, San Francisco, Berlin, and Oxford. Our teams bring together technical and multi-disciplinary expertise across the product lifecycle, and we’re hiring talent to help scale every part of the business. We work quickly to turn cutting-edge science into deployable technology.

In 2024 we raised US$113 million in Series B funding, the largest aggregate investment for a quantum software company. Six months later we delivered the first commercial quantum advantage with Ironstone Opal, our field-validated quantum navigation solution for defense and industry.

At Q-CTRL, we prioritize outcomes over hours. We offer flexibility, equity potential, and competitive benefits that reflect our high-performance culture. If you’re ready to help shape the future of quantum, we’d love to hear from you!

Please be advised that our communications will only come from the @q-ctrl.com domain. All our active job postings are available on our company website.

To recruitment agencies, we do not accept unsolicited branded profiles and are not responsible for any fees related to unsolicited resumes.

We may use artificial intelligence (AI) tools to support parts of the hiring process, such as reviewing applications, analyzing resumes, or assessing responses. These tools assist our recruitment team but do not replace human judgment. Final hiring decisions are ultimately made by humans. If you would like more information about how your data is processed, please contact us.

Job Title: Data / AI Consultant (Junior / Graduate) — Client Audits, AI Seals & GRC Support
Ad Text:

This is a hands-on role where you’ll work closely under the CEO on real client projects, combining technical execution with clear documentation and client-ready deliverables.

Key responsibilities

Contribute to AI Seals: readiness checks, controls mapping, documentation and findings

Assist with GRC client support: translate governance/risk requirements into practical technical actions

Data engineering support:

Build/validate ETL/ELT pipelines and data quality checks

Support data modelling and schema design

Support AI engineering activities as needed (data preparation, evaluation/monitoring concepts)

Skills & experience (must-have)

Data Engineering and AI Engineering fundamentals

Python (data wrangling, automation)

SQL (joins, CTEs, query fundamentals)

ETL/ELT knowledge (concepts and/or tools)

Data modelling knowledge

Suitable for

Graduates and early-career professionals

Candidates who enjoy technical problem-solving and want to grow in Data + AI + Governance/Assurance

How to apply

Email your CV and a short note to careers@giofai.com.au with the subject:
“Junior Data/AI Consultant – [Your Name]”

In your note, please include:

Your strongest cloud platform (AWS/Azure/GCP)

A project using Python + SQL + pipelines (uni/personal/professional)

Any exposure to governance, risk, controls or audits (if any)

Ad Text:
Solution Architect (Multiple)

Contract to 30/06/2026 with possible extension | Brisbane CBD + WFH

We are seeking three experienced Senior Solution Architect to support a Queensland Government department through a critical phase of enterprise transformation. These roles sit across Technology, Shared Services (Finance, Risk & HR), and Integration, and are focused on domain architecture, strategic direction, and stakeholder facilitation, rather than hands-on solution build.

You will play a key role in shaping current-state and target-state architectures, supporting upcoming go-to-market and procurement activities, and providing clear architectural guidance aligned to enterprise standards and government frameworks.

Key Responsibilities

Assess and document current-state architectures within assigned domains and define clear, achievable target-state architectures.

Contribute to the development and application of architecture principles, standards, and patterns, ensuring alignment with Enterprise Architecture (EA) governance frameworks and Queensland Government reference models.

Translate complex business and technical environments into clear architectural artefacts, including conceptual and logical designs.

Facilitate workshops and architecture discussions with senior business, technology, and delivery stakeholders to drive alignment and consensus.

Partner with leaders across business, technology, data, integration, infrastructure, and security domains to ensure cohesive, enterprise-aligned outcomes.

Support technology procurement and market engagement activities, including vendor briefings, evaluations, and high-level solution shaping.

What We’re Looking For

Demonstrated experience operating in enterprise or domain architecture roles, with a strong consulting and facilitation mindset.

Broad exposure to complex technology environments, platforms, and operating models, rather than deep engineering specialisation.

Experience working across one or more of the following domains:

Enterprise or technology services architecture

Shared services platforms (Finance, HR, Risk, ERP, HRIS)

Integration architecture, APIs, and data movement

Strong understanding of Enterprise Architecture (EA) principles, governance, and reference frameworks.

Experience supporting procurement activities, business cases, or go-to-market engagements.

Why apply through Lime Recruitment?

Enjoy two pay runs per week without contractor fees. As a Queensland-owned agency, we offer personalised service and are a Tier 1 supplier to the Queensland Government. Awarded Australia’s top-performing small agency in 2021 and 2022, with a finalist spot in 2023. Partner with Lime for genuine, experienced, friendly recruiters dedicated to securing the best opportunities for you. Apply now or contact Daniel Keyte on 0433 013 200 or daniel@limejobs.com.au to find out more!

Company Description

We welcome fearless thinkers

For over 100 years, Maurice Blackburn has stood up for those who need us most. With courage and compassion, we extend access to justice to countless Australians. We look beyond the immediate challenge to support people in moments that matter across their lives and continually push for better solutions for our clients. We invest in and empower our people to stand up for what we believe in and go fearlessly forward together.

We work on real cases, achieving important and positive results in real people’s lives, which is why we are one of Australia’s most respected law firms. Maurice Blackburn, experience you can count on. 

About the team and role

Maurice Blackburn has a bold ambition to redefine the way legal services are delivered in Australia, reimagining what justice means in a modern, digital and inclusive society. To deliver on this ambition, we established The Foundry to drive transformation through new business models, new partnerships and new capabilities.

Help us power smarter, faster, fairer outcomes by designing the integration fabric that connects agentic AI with our platforms and partners. As our Principal Engineer, you’ll set the engineering bar, ship production ready services, so the tools we build can make a real difference for the clients we serve.

You’ll lead how we engineer and operationalise agentic AI, creating robust patterns, CI/CD pipelines, testing strategies and observability that make experimentation safe and deployment repeatable. You’ll be hands on, solving interesting problems, mentoring engineers, and turning emerging ideas into working, scalable services.

You’ll report to the Head of Engineering – The Foundry, partner closely with our Digital & Technology team, and collaborate with external vendors. Expect autonomy, high trust, and a firm that backs smart engineering with clear purpose.

What you’ll do

Set standards & architecture: Define best practice patterns for integrating agentic AI with internal platforms and third-party services; publish reference designs that accelerate delivery.
Build the pipelines: Design CI/CD and test frameworks fit for AI workflows, including approaches for non‑deterministic outputs, plus monitoring and alerting in production.  
Lead by doing: Unblock complex technical issues, review code, and contribute directly to services built in Python and TypeScript.
Advocate for emerging tech: Stay active in industry communities and share learnings that lift capability across The Foundry and the broader business.

What you’ll bring

A problem solver’s mindset and the autonomy to debug complex systems end to end.
Strong hands-on engineering, with significant experience in building production grade services in Python and/or TypeScript.
Practical experience designing CI/CD pipelines, automation testing, API design, system integration, and cloud native development.
An ability to mentor, influence and communicate, bridging technical depth with business pragmatism.
Curiosity for AI/ML and the agentic AI landscape; you’re a continuous learner who engages with technical communities.

Ready to join us at the frontier of legal innovation, where bold ideas become transformative solutions and fearless thinkers shape the future of justice?

About the business

Fiercely proud of our unique Western Suburbs heritage – the Western Bulldogs have represented Melbourne’s West, our geographic heartland, for over 100 years. Our famous Bulldog fighting spirit mirrors that of the West – where hard work and standing up for what you believe in matters. While some things change, some stay the same. Our Club still exists to bring people together and create lasting memories, as much as it strives to win premierships. It’s about our people, and their shared passion for the red, white and blue. It’s about ambition, pride, determination, and having a place to call home. We’ll always be entrenched in our community, embracing the beauty and strength in its diversity. It’s the story of what it means to be a Bulldog ‘Through & Through’.




We strive to create an inclusive environment where all are celebrated and belong regardless of age, ability, gender, sexual orientation, religion or background. We are a child safe organisation committed to the safety and wellbeing of all children and young people. If you are looking to be a part of a committed and passionate team, the Western Bulldogs encourage you to apply for this fantastic role.




Your contribution to the team includes:

The Data Engineer will be responsible for designing, building and maintaining scalable data infrastructure and processes at the Western Bulldogs.




Reporting to the Head of Strategy and New Business, the role will work closely with all teams and departments at the Club to create data infrastructure which is connected, efficient, secure, and allows for in-depth analysis, valuable insights and informed decision making. The Data Engineer will play a pivotal role in informing and driving the strategic direction of data at the Club and will help to embed a data-driven culture.




The role will lead the implementation of the Club’s data warehouse and will be responsible for connecting the data warehouse to a host of applications, systems and technologies which collect Club data. They will hold knowledge of leading practice approaches to scalable data infrastructure and prioritise automation, reduction of manual handling and standardisation of data. The data warehouse produced will lay the foundations for advanced statistical modelling, analytics and reporting. It will be compliant with relevant data storage rules and regulations.




The role will work very closely with the Head of Strategy and New Business, and Data, Business and Performance Analysts to ensure the infrastructure is built and leveraged to its maximum capacity.




The Data Engineer will also hold important relationships with the AFL and relevant external parties.




This role is also responsible for:

Data Leadership - providing strategic vision and leadership for data governance, architecture, collection, storage and usage across the organisation
Data Engineering - designing, building, and maintaining scalable data infrastructure and processes
Bespoke Projects – working with various stakeholders to identify and respond to emerging organisational needs and trends.

Skills and experience

Formal tertiary qualification in a related field such as data engineering, computer science, data management, information systems or information technology.
At least 3 years in a strategic data engineering role.
Extensive experience in Cloud data implementation projects and in working with data warehouses.
Extensive experience in R, Python and SQL.
Experience working with data engineering tools, particularly Snowflake
Experience in strategic design for data systems.
Experience using API’s for data extraction
Experience working with emerging ELT data management and engineering technologies.
Demonstrated ability to apply AI technologies responsibly, with a proven history of delivering value through AI-driven projects.
Familiarity with a wide range of types of data from quantitative to qualitative to audio-visual
Experience working in sport / high performance environments desirable

Additional Work Life Leave - provided to those who are required to work weekends
Birthday Leave - a day of leave available in the week of your birthday
Close to West Footscray Station, with free onsite parking available

Continuous learning & development – Array of paid and discounted professional training and development opportunities on offer
Deals & Discounts with Club corporate sponsors - over 40% in some cases
Parent friendly – Paid Primary and Secondary Carer’s Leave available
Wellbeing focus including - we support our staff to complete a proactive wellbeing plan, access to club gym, wellbeing sessions and activities across the year

Overview

The AI Business Solution CSA team are positioned as end‑to‑end Copilot & Agentic AI advisors.  CSAs responsibilities include:

We are MMG and we mine for progress

Rosebery is an underground polymetallic base metal mine located in the township of Rosebery in Tasmania, Australia. The mine is a deep, sub-level open stoping operation with complex mining conditions.

The Rosebery Mine has been at the heart of the Rosebery community since 1936 and is one of Tasmania’s largest and oldest continuously operating, underground mines producing zinc, copper and lead concentrates, as well as gold doré.

It supports approximately 500 employees and their families, has a strong community focus and engages a wide range of local businesses from across Tasmania in its supply chain boosting the economy of the West Coast of Tasmania and beyond.

The mine has a strong future, with extensive exploration activities which have continued to grow the resource and require mine planning beyond 10 years of continued operation.

MMG Rosebery has an office in Burnie (Tasmania), giving employees the flexibility to work from there when they are not required onsite.

Control Systems Engineer

MMG Rosebery is currently recruiting a Control Systems Engineer on a 4:3 roster, DIDO or Residential to Rosebery, Tasmania.

You will possess an intimate knowledge of the Process Control System (PCS) and actively support operations and ensure process control functionality is of the highest quality, ultimately aiding the improvement in value recovery from the concentrator.

You will also be responsible for guiding the ongoing maintenance and optimisation of the SCADA/PLC system and ensuring the control system architecture is maintained for additions, changes and improvements.

Responsibilities Include (however not limited to):

Troubleshooting control equipment, automation, and instrumentation solutions, and managing their remediation.  
Integration of Process control data (OT) data into Process historians and OT systems to the IT systems to enhance data flow, improve system reliability, whilst strengthening cybersecurity posture.
Ensure process and control systems documentation is accurate and updated.  This is inclusive of P&IDs, wiring diagrams, Sops support documentation, high level specifications and functional description.
Maintain the environment ensuring adherence to change control, safety, and regulatory protocols. 
Adhere to change Management processes; guaranteeing the system architecture is maintained and the integrity of interfaces from the SCADA/historian to Mine Operating Systems are preserved. 
Coordinate with support vendors and Process Control Integrators to maintain and enhance the process control environment.
Implement and maintain process control software and databases. 
Support improvement initiatives in cybersecurity and the industrial control systems network.
Assist in the lifecycle management of control systems through regular inspections, projects, and preventive maintenance of control equipment.  
Consult with external Process Control Support Contractors involved in both project and support work functions. 
Provide ongoing support and guidance to key users of the Process Control System, facilitating training programs and mentoring of processing technical staff
Demonstrate safe behaviour at all times and comply with the site’s standards and procedures in SHEC whilst promoting best practises and a positive safety culture at all times. 

About You:

Minimum 5+ years site-based control system experience.
Previous exposure to DCS and PLC systems, Aveva Pi, as well as OPC and other industrial telecommunications.
Experience with industrial communication protocols with ControlNet, Device net, Ethernet, Modbus, Wireless, Fibre Optic and RTU communications highly desirable. 
Demonstrated ability to analyse and manage processing plant control system performance and undertake control loop tuning and alarm management to improve circuit operation and stability.
Demonstrated experience in identification and implementation of projects to maximise value recovery through improvements in the process control. 
Experience with working with process historians, with experience working with Aveva PI highly regarded.
Thorough understanding of Process Control System architecture, specifically Honeywell (Experion) DCS and/ or SCADA/ Rockwell PLC based systems including coding.
Ability to understand and interpret electrical drawings, process flow diagrams and P&ID's.
Sound knowledge of process control optimisation techniques, including but not limited to loop tuning and alarm management.
In depth understanding of process control system architecture and change management process required to preserve it. 
Possess strong customer focus and teamwork skills to listen, interact, influence and deploy.
Strong attention to detail, accuracy and initiative with the ability to work autonomously
An unwavering commitment to safe work practices with demonstrate safe behaviour at all times and comply with the site’s standards and procedures. 
A manual C Class driver’s license
First aid certificate – Desirable
Ability to pass a Police Clearance, Pre employment Medical and DAS.

What we offer

At Rosebery, our aim is to create a workplace that encourages diversity and inclusion and supports our people to grow.  We are guided by our values; think safety first, respect each other, work together, do what we say, and we want to be better.  We offer;

A safety-first culture

Family friendly rosters
Reward and Recognition Scheme
Bonus' including short term incentive program
Corporate Discount Programs & Novated Leasing – Utilize a range of discount programs (health insurance, travel).
Employee Assistance Program (EAP) that includes free confidential counselling, wellbeing services.
Relocation support

MMG has a global presence, owning and developing copper, zinc and other base metals projects across Australia, the Democratic Republic of the Congo, Peru and Botswana.

Our aim is to create a workplace that encourages diversity and inclusion and supports our people to grow.

We are guided by our values; think safety first, respect each other, work together, do what we say, and we want to be better.

Headquartered in Melbourne, we are listed on the Hong Kong Stock Exchange (HKEx 1208) with an international shareholder base.

As a company, MMG strives for the best in safety, environmental protection, production standards and overall operational excellence. We are an equal opportunity employer who values and respects diversity. We recognise the unique value your contribution makes to the progress of our company and the communities in which we operate.

Ad Text:

About the Carlton Football Club

The Carlton Football Club is one of Australia’s oldest and most prominent sport institutions. Founded in 1864, the Club’s headquarters and training facilities are located in Carlton at IKON Park, our traditional home ground. Our IKON Park redevelopment is now complete, and we are proud of our state-of-the-art facilities that supports our high-performance environment. When the Club set about undertaking this historic work, it was based upon achieving facilities for women’s sport that would be the equal of their male counterparts.

We are passionate about our contribution to the Community and foster an inclusive and welcoming culture where our values are at the core of who we are and what we do.

About the Role

Build and maintain scalable ETL/ELT data pipelines that connect diverse sources to the Club’s centralised data platform.

Implement robust data governance strategies to ensure the accuracy, usability, and accessibility of key datasets, while upholding data security best practices and maintain compliance with regulatory requirements.
Collaborate with key stakeholders across all teams providing support on data-related technical challenges, while educating colleagues on safe, secure data practices and responsible AI usage.
Develop and maintain clear, comprehensive documentation to guide the Club’s data users in leveraging new data sources and instructing on best practices.
Stay at the forefront of emerging technologies and AI, regularly researching trends, tools, and practices that could enhance the Club’s operations and performance.
Contribute to the evaluation and development of AI-driven proof of concepts, helping transform innovative ideas into practical solutions.
Collaborate with senior team members to identify opportunities for AI integration, supporting the implementation of innovative solutions to enhance productivity and decision-making across departments.
Participate in pilot projects and technology trials, gathering feedback and documenting outcomes to inform future adoption of new tools and platforms.
Share insights and findings with colleagues, helping to foster a culture of continuous learning and innovation around emerging technologies and AI within the Club.

Experience, Skills and Attributes

Undergraduate degree in mathematics, statistics, computer science, or any related field and/or equivalent experience
2+ years of previous work experience in data engineering or analytical role(s) (or similar).
Previous experience working in a sporting organisation is preferred, although not essential
Experience building and maintaining automated data pipelines from flat file and API-based sources, using ETL/ELT tools (Matillion, Fivetran, etc.), SQL, relevant programming languages including Python, and cloud platforms.
Experience working with and administering data warehouses, preferably Snowflake.
Experience with AWS cloud services and tools, such as RDS, EC2, and S3 buckets.
Familiarity with both Mac and Windows operating systems.
Proficiency with industry data quality standards (cleansing, validation, and governance).
Proficiency in creating and maintaining data documentation and version control systems.
Experience working with business intelligence/visualisation tools (e.g. Tableau, PowerBI)
Familiarity with Atlassian products (e.g. Confluence, Jira)
Strong communication skills and an ability to build positive working relationships with others.
Curious, innovative thinker with a highly developed analytical ability and strong problem-solving skills.
Highly self-motivated and proactive, with an ability to work both autonomously and collaboratively as part of a team.
Effective time management and stakeholder management skills, with a proven ability to manage multiple competing priorities.

Benefits and Culture

Carlton’s values underpin how the Club operates, describing how our people work together, interact and behave. The Club is passionate about its culture, focused on cultivating a unique sense of belonging and connection. In addition, we offer our people flexible working, learning and development opportunities, as well as employee benefits such as membership, café and retail discounts, alongside working in a world-class sporting amenity.

How to Apply

Please submit your current resume and cover letter addressed to the Data Analytics Manager by 11:55pm Sunday 11 January. Applicant shortlisting and interviews for this role will commence in mid-late January 2026.

The Carlton Football Club is an equal opportunity employer and a place who welcomes all. We encourage people with diverse experiences and backgrounds to apply. This includes, but is not limited to, those from the Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander, Culturally and Linguistically Diverse, and LGBTQIA+ communities. We are committed to fostering a workplace environment which is inclusive, safe, and flexible. All applicants will be considered based on the relevance of their abilities to the role and their alignment with our Club Values.

The Carlton Football Club is committed to providing a welcoming environment where the safety and wellbeing of all children and young people involved in our programs, services, activities, events, and the broader community, will always be our first priority. All staff must hold (or be willing to obtain) a current Victorian Working With Children Check as part of their employment with the Club.

A lot of data science roles talk about impact.
This one expects it.

You’ll be working on AI and GenAI powered features that sit directly in front of customers. Not internal dashboards. Not science projects. Actual product functionality where success is measured by whether it improves the experience and stands up in the real world.

This team is building ML and LLM driven capabilities into products used by thousands of customers. That brings real constraints, real trade offs, and real accountability. You’ll be working in domains where correctness, trust, and compliance matter as much as innovation.

They’ve moved past asking “can we do this?”.
Now the question is “is this the right thing to build, and how do we prove it works?”

What you’ll be doing This is an end to end role. If you like owning problems rather than just parts of them, you’ll feel at home.

Partnering closely with product managers to frame hypotheses and decide what’s worth building.
Designing experiments and evaluation approaches that run through the full product lifecycle, not just at launch.
Prototyping and validating GenAI and ML based solutions, then helping drive them through MVP and into production.
Working across NLP, retrieval, forecasting, recommendations and anomaly detection, depending on the product area.
Defining success metrics that matter to customers and the business, then using them to guide iteration.
Running offline evaluations and online experiments to understand real customer and commercial impact.
Working closely with ML Engineers and frontend teams to ship reliable, measurable and safe solutions.
Operating comfortably in regulated, risk aware environments where models need to behave predictably.
Sharing knowledge and influencing how data science is practiced beyond your own work.
You won’t be judged on how clever your model is. You’ll be judged on whether it improves the product.

Who this suits
You’ve shipped customer facing ML or GenAI features before. You’ve seen what happens when something goes live, and you understand how different that is from internal work.

Hands on GenAI experience is essential here. You’ve worked with LLM based systems, evaluation approaches, and the trade offs involved in deploying them to customers.

You bring a hypothesis driven mindset. You’re comfortable exploring complex systems, testing assumptions, and using evidence to guide decisions.
